######################################################################
# INSTALLATION
######################################################################

1. Install this extension
2. Activate the "Social Bookmarks" plugin
3. Add [socialbookmarks/] to your layout or to any page content
4. Save and reload a page, the social bookmarks menu should appear

All currently possible social-bookmark services:
digg,reddit,stumbleupon,delicious,technorati,furl,facebook,myspace,yahoo,script-style,blinklist,mixx,designfloat

Configuration:
==============
If you want to use only some services, customize your code to use [socialbookmarks]list-of-services[/socialbookmarks] instead.
"list-of-services" is a comma separated list of the services to use, e.g.: [socialbookmarks]facebook,digg,technorati,delicious[/socialbookmarks]


######################################################################
# CHANGELOG
######################################################################

Version 1.0
- compatibility with Bigace 3
- configurable sites
- no need for template customization, except of the [socialbookmarks/] code

Version 0.5
- css: added margin/padding 0 for ul.socials

Version 0.4
- Support {metatags} and content filter, no need for other template hooks

Version 0.3
- Fixed path for additional IE7 javascript

Version 0.2
- Added element to clear left floating

